[38;2;255;255;255mâº[39m Excellent! Now I can see the root cause clearly. The Student structure
  has:

  - [38;2;177;185;249mnum_scores = 0[39m (valid value)

  The problem is that [38;2;177;185;249mscores[39m is a NULL pointer (0x0), so when the code
  tries to access [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[s->num_scores][39m (which is [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[0][39m), it
  attempts to write to address 0x0, causing the crash.

[38;2;255;255;255mâº[39m Now I can provide the complete analysis of the crash:

  [1mRoot Cause Analysis[22m

  [1mWhere it crashes:[22m
  - Function: [38;2;177;185;249madd_score()[39m in [38;2;177;185;249mdemo-buggy.c:26:30[39m
  - Line: [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[s->num_scores] = score;[39m

  [1mWhy it crashes:[22m
  - [1mEXC_BAD_ACCESS (code=1, address=0x0)[22m - attempted to write to NULL
  pointer
  - The [38;2;177;185;249mscores[39m field in the Student structure is [38;2;177;185;249mNULL[39m (0x0000000000000000)
  - When [38;2;177;185;249madd_score()[39m tries to access [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[0][39m, it attempts to write to
  address 0x0, causing a segmentation fault

  [1mVariables at crash:[22m
  - [38;2;177;185;249ms->name = "Alice"[39m (valid)
  - [38;2;177;185;249ms->age = 20[39m (valid)
  - [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores = 0x0000000000000000[39m (NULL - this is the problem!)
  - [38;2;177;185;249ms->num_scores = 0[39m (valid)
  - [38;2;177;185;249mscore = 95.5[39m (valid)

  [1mCall Stack:[22m
  1. [38;2;177;185;249mmain()[39m at line 56: [38;2;177;185;249madd_score(alice, 95.5)[39m
  2. [38;2;177;185;249madd_score()[39m at line 26: [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[s->num_scores] = score[39m

  [1mSource of the bug:[22m
  In the [38;2;177;185;249mcreate_student()[39m function (demo-buggy.c:19), the scores array is
  intentionally set to NULL:
  s->scores = [34mNULL[39m;  [32m// This will cause a segfault when we try to write to [39m
  [32mit[39m

  The commented-out line 18 shows the correct allocation that should
  happen:
  [32m// s->scores = malloc(100 * sizeof(float));  // Allocate space for 100 [39m
  [32mscores[39m

  [1mRoot cause:[22m The [38;2;177;185;249mcreate_student()[39m function fails to allocate memory for
  the [38;2;177;185;249mscores[39m array, leaving it as a NULL pointer. When [38;2;177;185;249madd_score()[39m attempts
   to write to [38;2;177;185;249mscores[0][39m, it tries to dereference a NULL pointer, causing
  the program to crash with a segmentation fault.
